NaturalSetCollection

public NaturalSetCollection(NaturalDomain domain,
                            int size,
                            boolean populate)
Constructs a collection with an initial capacity for size elements. If populate is true the resulting object is populated with empty NaturalSet objects.

Parameters:
domain - The NaturalDomain all sets in the collection must be defined on.
size - Initial capacity of the collection. In case populate is true this is the number of empty sets the collection is populated with.
populate - Singals if to populate the collection with empty sets.
